## Flag → Test Rules

Rules used by `/qa-plan-client` to determine which tests apply to a given client.
Source of flags: `data/qa-matrix.json` (generated by `mongo-extractor.py`).

### Always Apply (every client, every QA session)

| Test | Tool | Why |
|------|------|-----|
| `login.spec.ts` | Playwright | C1 — auth is always critical |
| `config-validation.spec.ts` | Playwright | Multi-client config regression |
| `cart.spec.ts` | Playwright | C2 — order creation always critical |
| `checkout.spec.ts` | Playwright | C2 — checkout always critical |
| `checklist-regresion-postmortems.md` | Checklist | PM1-PM7 — pre-deploy always |
| COWORK: C1, C2 flows | Cowork | Login + full purchase always |
| Maestro: 01-login.yaml | Maestro | APP auth always |
| Maestro: 05-pedido.yaml | Maestro | APP order always |

### Conditional — by Client Flag

| Flag | Value | Add These Tests |
|------|-------|-----------------|
| `enableCoupons` | `true` | `coupons.spec.ts` · COWORK: C3-14, C3-15 |
| `enableKhipu` / `payment.enableKhipu` | `true` | `checklist-fintech-khipu.md` · COWORK: verificar opción Khipu en checkout |
| `enablePaymentDocumentsB2B` | `true` | `payments.spec.ts` · COWORK: C7-10, C7-11, C7-12 |
| `enableInvoicesList` | `true` | COWORK: C7-11 (menú facturas) |
| `pendingDocuments` | `true` | COWORK: C7-12 (badge documentos) |
| `enableOrderApproval` | `true` | COWORK: Flujo 5 (botón aprobar en /orders) |
| `purchaseOrderEnabled` | `true` | COWORK: validar campo OC en checkout (C2-11) |
| `editAddress` | `false` | COWORK: validar dirección locked en checkout |
| `hasStockEnabled` | `true` | COWORK: validar stock en tarjetas (C2-01) |
| `hasAllDistributionCenters` | `true` | COWORK: validar botón "Ver stock" multicentro |
| `enableSellerDiscount` | `true` | COWORK: validar campo descuento en carrito |
| `disableCommerceEdit` | `true` | COWORK: Flujo 3 (perfil locked) |
| `anonymousAccess` | `true` | COWORK: probar catálogo sin login |
| `enableCreditNotes` | `true` | `checklist-deuda-tecnica-pagos.md` |
| `enableOrderValidation` | `true` | COWORK: C2-12 (doble submit + validación) |
| ERP hooks configurados | any | `checklist-integraciones-erp.md` · `checklist-webhooks.md` · COWORK: C4-09 |
| `pricing.stepPricing` exists | any | `step-pricing.spec.ts` · `prices.spec.ts` |
| `promotions` exist | any | `promotions.spec.ts` · COWORK: C3-02 |
| `enablePriceOracle` | `true` | COWORK: validar precio cambia con fecha de entrega |

### Never Apply (skip if flag is absent or false)

| Condition | Skip |
|-----------|------|
| `enableKhipu = false` | `checklist-fintech-khipu.md` |
| `enablePaymentDocumentsB2B = false` | C7-10, C7-11, C7-12 |
| `enableCoupons = false` | `coupons.spec.ts`, C3-14, C3-15 |
| No ERP hooks configured | `checklist-integraciones-erp.md`, `checklist-webhooks.md` |
| APP not deployed for client | All Maestro flows |

## Contract Testing

Validación de tipos en los datos de `clients.ts` antes de que lleguen a los tests E2E. Previene bugs silenciosos como BAS-QA-006 (`taxes.taxRate: 19` en vez de `0.19`).

### Arquitectura de 3 capas

```
MongoDB → mongo-extractor.py → qa-matrix-staging.json
                                     ↓
          sync-clients.py validate_client_variables()   ← Capa 1: warnings Python
                                     ↓
                         clients.ts (auto-generado)
                                     ↓
             tests/e2e/b2b/00-contract.spec.ts           ← Capa 2: assertions Playwright
                                     ↓
                  E2E specs (cart, cv-*, checkout…)      ← Capa 3: lógica de negocio
```

**Schema fuente de verdad:** `data/schemas/client-variables.schema.json`

### Capa 1 — Python (sync-clients.py)

- Corre automáticamente con `python3 tools/sync-clients.py`
- **No-blocking:** imprime `[CONTRACT WARN]` pero continúa generando `clients.ts`
- Valida todos los clientes del JSON (incluyendo inactivos)
- Formato de warning: `[CONTRACT WARN] {client-key} / {field}: expected bool, got str 'true'`

### Capa 2 — Playwright (00-contract.spec.ts)

- Tests de datos puros — **sin browser, sin red, sin `page` fixture**
- Nombre `00-` para aparecer primero en reportes
- Itera `Object.entries(clients)` — cubre todos los clientes automáticamente
- Ejecutar solo contratos: `npx playwright test b2b/00-contract.spec.ts --project=b2b`

### Campos del contrato

| Campo | Tipo | Regla |
|-------|------|-------|
| `taxes.taxRate` | `number` | Rango `[0, 1]` — `0.19` no `19` (BAS-QA-006) |
| 39 boolean flags | `boolean` | Nunca `string` ni `number` |

### Agregar nuevo campo al contrato

1. Agregar en `data/schemas/client-variables.schema.json` bajo `"properties"`
2. Si es boolean: agregar a `_CONTRACT_BOOL_FIELDS` en `tools/sync-clients.py` y a `BOOL_FIELDS` en `tests/e2e/b2b/00-contract.spec.ts`
3. Si es numérico/enum: agregar bloque explícito en `validate_client_variables()` y nuevo `test()` en el spec

### Gate recomendado para CI

```bash
# Paso 1: contrato (rápido, sin browser)
npx playwright test b2b/00-contract.spec.ts --project=b2b
# Paso 2: suite completa (solo si paso 1 pasa)
npx playwright test --project=b2b
```

